---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "2026-06-19";
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie policy" description="What cookies Journal uses.">
	<header class="container-prose page-head">
		<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Journal</a> / <a href="/legal/">Legal</a> / Cookies</p>
		<h1>Cookie policy</h1>
		<p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
	</header>

	<article class="container-prose prose">
		<p>
			Journal uses the smallest set of cookies and storage we can get away
			with. Most state lives in your own browser.
		</p>

		<h2>What we set</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Theme</strong> — <code>localStorage</code> key
				<code>theme</code> remembers light / dark / system. No tracking.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Editor + UI preferences</strong> — Journal stores autosave
				cadence, recent journals, last-opened entry, and similar preferences
				in <code>localStorage</code> under namespaced keys (e.g.
				<code>journal:editor</code>). They never leave your device.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Auth session</strong> — when you sign in, Firebase
				Authentication sets cookies on <code>auth.oriz.in</code> so you stay
				logged in across every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site. These are
				first-party and essential.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>PWA cache</strong> — the service worker caches assets
				(scripts, styles, fonts, images) in the browser's Cache Storage so
				Journal works offline. No tracking; expires automatically.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Third parties</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Cloudflare</strong> may set anti-abuse cookies (Turnstile, bot
				management). These are essential for site availability.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Google AdSense</strong> (once approved) may set advertising
				cookies. The consent banner lets you opt out per-purpose.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Opting out</h2>
		<p>
			Clear localStorage and cookies for <code>journal.oriz.in</code> from
			your browser's site-data settings. Theme, preferences, and auth will
			reset. Your Firestore data is untouched — to delete that, use account
			deletion in Settings.
		</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.page-head {
		padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule, #d9d0bd);
	}
	.eyebrow {
		color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256);
		font-size: 0.8125rem;
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
	}
	.eyebrow a { color: var(--color-ink-muted, #6b6256); text-decoration: none; }
	h1 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.meta { color: var(--color-ink-subtle, #9a9082); font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0; }
	.prose {
		padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		font-size: 1.0625rem;
	}
	.prose h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-display, "Fraunces", serif);
		font-size: 1.375rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
	}
	.prose ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
	.prose li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
	.prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
	.prose a { color: var(--color-sienna, #b45309); }
	.prose code {
		background: var(--color-paper-soft, #f1ece2);
		padding: 0.125em 0.375em;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
		font-size: 0.875em;
	}
	.container-prose {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin-inline: auto;
		padding-inline: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 2rem);
	}
</style>
